title: The Latest: Small tsunami triggered by quake reaches Alaska
text: The National Tsunami Warning Center says King Cove, Alaska, reported water heights of six-tenths of a foot late Tuesday morning. A tsunami advisory has been dropped for Hawaii after a powerful earthquake off Chile, but it remains in effect for parts of coastal California. The National Tsunami Warning Center says an advisory remains in effect for Ragged Point, California and San Onofre State Beach, California. Â»
